column1: % South Pole SPO (90S).
% Replicate sample mean Siemens CO2 values.
% Aspirated and Non-aspirated
%    From archive dated 08-Nov-2018 17:00:58
% This files contains the average of flask replicates collected on a given day.
% Flasks identified as outliers during workup or that are more than 0.25ppm from sample
% mean are flagged as outliers and excluded from average
% COLUMN DEFINITIONS:
% Columns 1 and 2 are the sampling date and time (UTC).
% Column 3 is the Siemens CO2 replicate mean value in ppm
% Column 4 is the standard deviation of the retained replications
% Column 5 is the number of retained replicates
% Columns 6 and 7 are the dates Excel and decimal formats.
% Column 8 is a flag for identifying uncertainty in the reported sampling time.
%   All sampling date/times are nominally corrected to UTC. But in some cases
%   the relevant correction is uncertain due to incomplete information on the
%   original sample log sheets. In this case Column 8 gives the (assumed)
%   correction applied (in hours). The flag is otherwise set to"UTC" indicating
%   that the time is not uncertain.
% Column 9 is a 3-letter station identifier.
% Column 10 is the value of a stiff spline fitted through the data
% Column 11 is the difference between the data and the stiff spline
%     Date
